  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7015.8 sitting right at the max negative gamma strike (-2225.7M), dealers are actively buying this dip to hedge their short gamma exposure, providing immediate support. The PIN regime with massive positive gamma walls at 7000 (+10.0B) and 7050 (+9.6B) creates a strong magnet effect that should pull price back toward the 7000-7030 range where dealers will flip to selling pressure. Watch for rejection at the 7000 level as dealers become net sellers above this key gamma wall, while any break below 6895 (GEX flip) would shift the entire regime bearish.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect a bounce back toward 7000 with resistance there capping upside.",
